# 6. アイドル大戦争！

Arisa: Alright, it's time for...! idol...
Group Members: Hazard!!!
Arisa: This week's MCs will be the lead of Cheerful * Days, myself, Arisa Higure, and—!
Marina: Marina Yamashita, one of the new additions from the fourth generation!
Minori: I-I-I-I-It's finally starting...!
Haruka: We're not supposed to appear for a while, so let's relax and just watch as spectators until then.
Minori: H-How are you able to stay so calm, Haruka...?! It feels like my heart's about to burst out of my chest...!
Airi: Says the girl who was chowing down on snacks in the green room until just a second ago. You're not gonna last very long at this rate.
Shizuku: Don't worry, Minori. Just try to remember what we discussed during our meeting.
Shizuku: I'm sure you'll feel much better once you do.
Minori: R-Right! Just focus on myself...!
Minori: I want to get my name out there... So I can spread hope to as many people as I can...
Airi: Now it sounds like she's chanting something...
Haruka: But I think it's working.
Marina: And I've been hooked on this stuff called “drinkable cake” lately because having actual cake late at night is like the opposite of eating healthy, you know?!
Arisa: Yeah, I know what you mean. But doesn't that mean you're still taking in the same amount of calories?
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Marina: That's the thing! They use really low-fat cream, which means I can have as much as I like!
Arisa: “As much as you like” doesn't mean less calories!
Arisa: Still, Marina, you really do love sweets, don't you? It's almost your birthday, so why don't you make a little request to your fans out there?
Marina: Wait, you mean it?! Then, I'll take this opportunity to tell them that... I want lots and lots of snacks and treats♪
Shizuku: (Arisa's improved quite a bit as an MC...)
Shizuku: (She must be working very hard considering how many different programs she's been appearing on lately.)
Shizuku: (Not only that, but everyone on the big panel...)
Group Members: Slow down, Marina! Don't forget that we're not really allowed to ask people to give us food!
Group Members: Also, what happened to the fourth generation being the new kids on the block? You seem pretty used to being in the spotlight, Marina! Are you sure you're really a rookie?
Shizuku: (They know how to throw in funny quips and jabs at the right moments. They're working very well together to the show's benefit. Which reinforces how...)
Arisa: Alright, settle down. That's the sort of banter iHaz needs, but no more ganging up on the new girl. So, for our next segment...!
Shizuku: (I really shouldn't have been the lead of Cheerful * Days back then...)
Shizuku: (I was supposed to just do as I was told, but I really only followed the scripts they gave me... I had no ability to actually speak for myself...)
Shizuku: (Even that didn't go well on a number of occasions, and the others were forced to save me.)
Shizuku: (My mind was so overwhelmed by having to play the “perfect” Shizuku Hinomori...)
Shizuku: (But...)
Shizuku: (I'm not that girl anymore.)
Arisa: You were given a once-in-a-lifetime opportunity that the rest of us would do anything for, but you don't seem to care whatsoever about capitalizing on it.
Shizuku: (That time, I didn't fully comprehend what she meant...)
Shizuku: (But now, I...)
Staff: MORE MORE JUMP! You're on standby!
Minori: ...!
Airi: This is it.
Airi: Ready, everyone...?!
Haruka: Yes. I'm ready whenever.
Minori: I-I-I-I-I'm ready...!
Airi: I'm looking forward to seeing how you do in front of the cameras, Minori, but...
Airi: How about you, Shizuku? It's been a while since you've been on TV.
Shizuku: I'm ready.
Shizuku: It's been a long time since I last did this, but let's try to make the most of it.
Airi: Sounds good. Then, let's go!
Arisa: Next, we have the mini segment that's all the rage right now! It's another edition of “Feature the Future” brought to you today by Marina and Arisa!
Marina: So, let's bring in our guests! Give a big round of applause for MORE MORE JUMP!
Minori: (Uh... The script said... Oh, we start by introducing ourselves...!)
Minori: Don't give up on your dreams, Minorinrin! Here's a bouquet of hope for you! Hello! I'm Minori Hanasato from MORE MORE JUMP!
Haruka: No matter how far, may this song of hope reach you! I'm Haruka Kiritani from MORE MORE JUMP!
Airi: One special delivery of love coming right up!
Airi: It's the lovely fairy, Airi! Airi Momoi from MORE MORE JUMP! at your service!
Shizuku: Here to bring you a burst of happiness. I'm Shizuku Hinomori from MORE MORE JUMP!
Shizuku: This is our first time appearing on TV together, so...
Minori, Haruka, Shizuku & Airi: Thank you for having us!
Marina: Wow! MORE MORE JUMP! in the flesh! Welcome to idol Hazard!
Arisa: We've been looking forward to having you on!
Arisa: Actually, mind if we talk like normal for this? I mean, I feel pretty awkward speaking so formally...
Shizuku: (Oh...)
Arisa: Again, there's no need to act so formal here. After all, we're members of the same group. Also...
Shizuku: Yes, of course...
Marina: You guys sound like you all go to the same high school or something. You've met some of them before, right, Arisa?
Arisa: Yeah, I've worked with Airi before when she was still with QT. Them and Cheerful * Days are managed by the same agency.
Airi: Yeah, that takes me back... Remember when both our groups did that big sports day event together?
Arisa: However, Haruka, Minori, we may or may not have crossed paths before, but this is essentially our first time talking to one another.
Haruka: Yes, it is... We've been looking forward to seeing you today.
Arisa: Likewise! And there's no need for either of you to be formal with me. That just leaves...
Arisa: I believe our viewers are more than aware that Shizuku and I have some history.
Shizuku: Yes, well...
Marina: Yeah, Shizuku, you used to be in Cheerful * Days, right?! You moved on before I joined, so this is my first time seeing you in person!
Arisa: No, she didn't “move on”. She left us behind!
Airi: Whoa! Really?! Now?! Our segment literally just started!
Haruka: Honestly. We haven't even had a chance to sit down yet.
Arisa: Oh, sorry! My bad! I got a little ahead of myself since we have so much to discuss.
Arisa: Anyway, please, take your seats! There are several questions that I want to ask since we don't see each other often.
Arisa: I have to think our viewers are beyond excited about Cheerful * Days and MORE MORE JUMP! appearing together today.
Shizuku: Yes, I agree. I've been looking forward to speaking with you and the others today.
Haruka: (I had a feeling that it was going to get a bit heated today, but she seems eager to go right at us.)
Airi: (Shizuku leaving wasn't a good thing for them either. The agency must've seen the script for this, so a part of me hoped that they'd keep their idols from going too far.)
Airi: (I definitely underestimated this girl. Also...)
iHaz Producer: iHaz has earned its reputation for featuring raw and uncut conversations between idols. Surprise stories are always welcome, so...
iHaz Producer: So we're actually looking forward to seeing how you and the MCs interact.
Airi: (Yeah, that's television for you... We came knowing that something like this could happen.)
Airi: (But...)
Airi: (Is Shizuku really gonna be okay...?)
